<item>
            <title>[GROOVY-643] HOME not quoted in groovysh</title>
                <link>https://issues.apache.org/jira/browse/GROOVY-643</link>
                <project id="12318123" key="GROOVY">Groovy</project>
                    <description>&lt;p&gt;from: Alan Thompson &amp;lt;groovy.user@whitecaps.net&amp;gt;&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;Hi - I&apos;m a new groovy user and just found a small bug installing Groovy&lt;br/&gt;
1.0-beta-7 on Cygwin.  The use of the $HOME environment variable at the end&lt;br/&gt;
of the groovysh script is not quoted (unlike most other env var&apos;s in the&lt;br/&gt;
script), which leads to problems on windoze since the default value of&lt;br/&gt;
$HOME is something like &quot;/home/Alan Thompson&quot;.  By simply changing line 140&lt;br/&gt;
(4&apos;th from last) of the groovysh script to read:&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;        -Djava.library.path=&quot;$HOME/.groovy/lib&quot; \&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;(note the added double quotes), it works fine.&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;This small fix should probably be added for Beta-8.&lt;/p&gt;</description>
